</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="76" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="76">South African distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="76">
East coast of South Africa, off Park Rynie (
<geoCoordinate direction="south" orientation="latitude" precision="5" value="-30.3187">30.3187°S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="5" value="30.7425">30.7425°E</geoCoordinate>
: approximate co-ordinates).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="76" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="76">
According to our present material, the ocular plates I and V appeared to be insert, which would be consistent with what is observed in other specimens of this species. This is the first South African record, representing a range extension southwards of this species from Madagascar (
<bibRefCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Clark and Rowe 1971</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
